pullRequest.body:
This is the first part of the proof of the main theorem of polytopes done in https://github.com/Jun2M/Main-theorem-of-polytopes

It introduces Halfspace type, its SetLike instance and a few simple lemmas.

Thanks for your PR! Did you mean to make your pull request as ready for review? If so, please add the label `awaiting-review`.

I see you have a few linter failures - don't hestitate to ask if the error messages are unclear. Once you have these and you get a green checkmark, the PR will appear in the review queue - where it's more likely to receive attention.
Do we need `InnerProductSpace` for this? Note that, e.g., `Real × Real` is not an inner product space. In any space, we can take a dual vector. Also, please use `Type*`, not `Type`.
